✨Long Post Alert✨ 

Today is the day I’ve not been looking forward to for the past month... but also a very happy day for many reasons. 😭

The man who has trained 3 of my horses Mike Moser Quarter Horses is moving to Florida for an amazing opportunity. I have been so blessed to have had Mike and Rhea in my life for the past 4 years. 

Mike is more than an incredible horse trainer to me. He’s a mentor, a coach, and someone to look up to. The amount of respect I have for Mike doesn’t have a number or a word to describe it. I was a nobody horse client who literally knew nothing or anyone of importance in the ranch riding/reining world. I was a good rider- but not in comparison to the horsemanship in this industry. He took me under his wing, taught me everything, introduced me to people, gave me advice, let me bother him with 27292974929 questions any time of the week. He made time for me. He made me feel like I was just as important as the client with a 100k horse. In the horse world where trainers shuck all of their horses off on their lopers and associates to ride and train- Mike is a rare find. He cares about the client and more than anything- he cares about the horse. 

I’ve seen him take lame horses and make them whole again. I’ve seen him take the 2 year old without the champion bloodlines and make them a winner. I’ve seen him take blown up reiners and make them calm. I’ve seen him teach a horse a completley new discipline. And I’ve seen him take that ”nobody” client to being a World Champion! 🏆🥇 Truly a little horse girls dream. 

I will miss Mike and Rhea, and selfishly I want them to stay. But I know they both deserve the world and the opportunity that awaits them in Florida is undeniably the best move. So I am very happy for them. I am also happy to take Phoenix out of training for awhile and get to spend some extra time with her @4heartsranch ! Logan and I will be able to ride Emmett and Phoenix together, and she will get some extra time to be a horse until we decide what that next move is. 👏🏽 

We love you Mike. We will be visiting… & I can’t wait to see what the future holds for you! ❤️

#WorldChampion #APHA #AQHA #RanchRiding #Reining #RanchHorse

Steelys Winter One-derland ❄️☃️ was absolutley magical this past Saturday! We got to celebrate with so many friends and family members. Watching all of the people you love in a room love on your baby is one of the best gifts! 💙

I can’t believe our little princess is ONE! 👑 This year went by so fast. Watching Steely grow has been the best experience of my life. When people say you won’t understand it until you have a kid…. They mean it. The love for your child is so unimaginably strong, I could have never in my wildest dreams been able to describe it. 🥹🥰

Thank you to everyone who came, wished her a happy birthday or sent something! We appreciate all of you! 🫶🏻

2023 was a heck of a year with ALOT of changes and accomplishments! 

It was my first full year of being a mom and a wife. ❤️💍

Work had the most inconsistent up and down roller coaster of sales and market in many years for me personally. 🎢 

Three of Logan and I’s best friends got married. 👩🏻‍❤️‍💋‍👨🏻 

My first niece was born. 👶🏻 

I won an APHA world championship with my mare. 🏆 

Celebrated our first wedding anniversary in Fredericksburg! 🍷

My trainer moved to Florida so I decided to stop showing for awhile and focus on other life goals. ❤️‍🩹 

We Celebrated Steely’s first birthday! 🎉🎁 

My best friend Janelle Kate Oles decided she HADDD to move back home to Naples, FL and leave me. 😭 (But seriously so happy for her) 🫶🏻

Oh ya- &&& SURPRISE we are moving to Aledo, TX! 🤗 🚛 We bought some land with a super nice horse barn and a little farm house that we plan on renovating and adding about 2000 square feet to! It’s going to be a work in progress and Definitley take time. But we are excited! (I’ll make a post more about this later haha) 🛠️💰🏡

All in all it was a great year….But I am ready for the joys and new adventures of 2024! ✨🍾✨
